---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { withBase } from "../lib/site";
---

<Base
  title="About me"
  section="about"
  description="Who's assembling Watermark, and why."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <p>
      <a href={withBase("/about")}>← About the project</a>
    </p>
    <h1>About me</h1>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Watermark is assembled by an independent researcher working entirely from
      public records — documents the developer didn't write.
    </p>

    <p>
      This page is a placeholder for a fuller note. For now, the method <em>is</em> the
      bio: every figure on this site is read from a primary source, validated against a
      typed schema, tagged for confidence, and linked back so you never have to take my
      word for it. If something here is wrong, that's a record to correct, not a verdict
      to defend.
    </p>

    <ul class="about-principles">
      <li>
        <strong>Independent.</strong> No affiliation with the developer, the county, or
        any party to the project — this is public-records research, not advocacy.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Reachable.</strong> Found an error, or have a document the record is
        missing? <a href={withBase("/submit")}>Submit a tip or correction →</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Accountable to the source.</strong> The standard is the same one I hold
        the record to: cite it, or don't claim it. Read the
        <a href={withBase("/bosc/docs/methodology")}>methodology</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Base>
